4:
Thanks again for your help today,
Klaus. I hope I'm not asking too
much of you.
6: You're not. What else can I do?
9:
Hehe, that's it for today. I'll see you
tomorrow.
15:
Ah, just prepping for tomorrow. 
Your salesmanship has really 
increased sales, 
so I'm making extra cookies.
21:
Really? Thank you! Then could you
sift all the flour in that bowl?
28:
H-hey, uhh... Everything okay? You've
been staring at me for a while now.
31:
Pay me no mind. I'm just studying
your baking skills... How does this
turn into food?
37:
W-wait... Does this mean I have a
new cooking buddy? I'll teach you
everything I know, and then we can
swap recipes!
42:
No... I am merely collecting
information. I made a mistake in the
store today and covered the entire
kitchen in flour.
45:
Even the slightest error could prove
fatal. If I am to fulfill my duties
without issue, I need to know more
about baking.
49:
G-gotcha. Then how about helping
me out? There's no better way to
learn than with first-hand
experience.
55:
Getting my hands dirty, huh? 
All right.
59:
You don't need to watch over the
dough. Just leave the rest to the
oven.
67: Is helping out at the sweet shop fun?
75:
But whenever I'm there, I feel the
urge to do something... anything.
80:
I see... Helping others makes me
happy too.
88:
I mean... The only one who can say
for sure is you, Klaus.
95: The dough is beginning to rise.
100:
Once it's ready, we should call
Nimbus and Albert over and eat
together. I'm sure they'd love that.
110:
Thank you for all your help these
past few days, Klaus.
112:
It's not much, but... consider it a
reward for a job well-done.
118:
Yup! I decorated it to look like you.
The white parts of your fur are
perfect for White Fest!
121:
...I see. It seems my work here is
done.
125:
Hey, Klaus! Another day of hard
work, huh?
134:
Alk, this is a thank-you gift for
teaching me to bake.
140:
Whoa, hold on, that girl made this
especially for you, didn't she? I can't
take that.
150:
Yeah, she did. Don't just re-gift it all
willy-nilly.
155:
Look at the icing work on this thing.
She really went all out. I'm sure it
took her a long, long time.
159:
I see... In other words, I now owe her
a debt.
163: And I always repay my debts.
168:
I, uh... don't think that's the case
here...
171:
Say... Did you get a look at the
cookie? Do you think she...
175:
Even if she does, there's no way that
numbskull would notice.
180:
Yeah, he's so innocent. It's kinda
ironic.
184:
You better give him lots of baking
and cooking advice. Really load him
up on debts to repay.
